  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem \r\n\r\nThe purge script `make nix-purge` often fails with \r\n\r\n```log\r\nAre you sure you want to purge Nix?\r\n[y/n]: y\r\nDetected multi-user Nix installation.\r\n/Library/LaunchDaemons/org.nixos.darwin-store.plist: Could not find specified service\r\nUnload failed: 113: Could not find specified service\r\nmake: *** [nix-purge] Error 3\r\n```\r\n\r\nand other times it fails with \r\n\r\n```log\r\nDetected multi-user Nix installation.\r\nStarted APFS operation\r\nDeleting APFS Volume from its APFS Container\r\nUnmounting disk3s7\r\nThe volume \"Nix Store\" on disk3s7 couldn't be unmounted because it is in use by process 0 (kernel)\r\nError: -69888: Couldn't unmount disk\r\n```\r\n\r\nas reported by @flexsurfer on macOS rosetta terminal. \r\n\r\nIt would be better if the make command for nix purge can handle these errors and allow us to re-run the purge command without doing `/nix/scripts/purge.sh --force`...\r\n",
